<br>
        It was told that long ago there was a staff, which held great power.  It was called The Crystal Staff.  Now, it was called so for a good reason.  The source of its power was four crystals.  The crystals were bound together.  No mortal could separate them.  These four crystals together, made an unimaginable force.  Now whether this power be good, or evil, all depended on the heart of the holder.<br>
<br>
        Legend does not tell of how this staff has come to be.  It may be written somewhere, but no one of present stature knows of its creation.  It does, however, tell of the staff’s power.  <br>
<br>
        The Kingdom of Thudro Orcsbane was once a very prosperous dwarven settlement.  Deep within the mountains of Everfrost was where this place once was.  I saw once, because no longer is it there.  <br>
<br>
        Long ago, as the dwarf’s were busy searching for their treasure, an unseen enemy snuck into the Kingdom.  This enemy was not unseen because of any special spell.  No, with the Crystal Staff in his possession, invisibility was his will.  One by one this enemy struck down the dwarves, completely unnoticed.  As the death toll grew, one dwarf saw what was happening to his friends.  Quick to finish his ale, he jumped up and alerted the<br>
rest of  the dwarves near by.  But useless it all was.  With a wave the unseen attacker shot a wall of fire, that killed every last dwarf.  The kingdom was burnt down.  The king, clutching onto his treasure chest, was buried amongst the rubble.  <br>
<br>
